CHAT BOT MAKING USING FLUTTERFLOW
ChatGPT said:

Creating a chatbot using FlutterFlow is a great way to build a visually appealing mobile or web app without deep coding skills. FlutterFlow allows integration with APIs and Firebase, which you can use to power your chatbot backend (e.g., OpenAI GPT, Dialogflow, or your custom logic).

🔧 STEP-BY-STEP GUIDE TO MAKING A CHATBOT IN FLUTTERFLOW

🧱 1. Set Up Your FlutterFlow Project

  • Go to https://flutterflow.io and create a new project.

  • Choose a blank app or a chat app template (recommended for chatbots).

💬 2. Design the Chat Interface

  • Page: Create a ChatPage.

  • UI Elements:

    • A ListView to display messages (from user and bot).

    • A TextField for input.

    • A Send button (or icon).

🧠 3. Choose a Backend for Chatbot Logic

You have 3 options:

✅ Option A: Dialogflow

  • Create a chatbot using Dialogflow.

  • Enable Webhook in Dialogflow for custom responses.

  • Integrate via REST API in FlutterFlow.

✅ Option B: OpenAI (ChatGPT API)

  • Create an account on platform.openai.com.

  • Use https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions.

  • Make API call from FlutterFlow’s API Call Section.

✅ Option C: Firebase Function/Custom Backend

  • Use Firebase Cloud Functions for processing.

  • FlutterFlow integrates directly with Firebase.

⚙️ 4. API Integration in FlutterFlow

📡 Define an API Call:

  • Go to API Calls tab.

  • Create a new API call (e.g., GetBotResponse).

  • Use:

    bash
    URL: https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions
Method: POST
Headers:
  Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY
  Content-Type: application/json
Body:
  {
    "model": "gpt-3.5-turbo",
    "messages": [
       {"role": "user", "content": "$userMessage"}
    ]
  }

  • Add $userMessage as a dynamic parameter.

🔄 5. Connect API to UI

  • On Send button tap:

    • Save TextField value to a local state variable userMessage.

    • Call the GetBotResponse API.

    • Store bot response in another variable (e.g., botReply).

    • Add both messages to a chat message list (local or Firebase).

🗂 6. Display Messages

  • Use a ListView bound to a list of messages.

  • Style messages based on sender (user or bot).

🔥 7. (Optional) Use Firebase for Real-Time Chat Saving

  • Set up Firestore with a Messages collection.

  • On each message send, push data to Firestore.

  • Bind ListView to Firestore for real-time sync.

📱 OUTPUT: A Chatbot App!

Once done, your app can:

  • Take input

  • Get a reply from AI

  • Display the conversation in a chat view

💡 Ideas for Use Cases

  • Perfume suggestion bot (as you mentioned earlier)

  • Customer support bot

  • Product recommender

  • FAQ bot

🧠 Step-by-Step: Build a Chatbot for ITRA Bazaar on Instagram & WhatsApp

🎯 GOAL:
Let users chat to find their ideal perfume — based on mood, occasion, and scent preference — and give product recommendations.

—

✅ 1. Set Up Business Accounts

Instagram:

  • Make sure your Instagram is a Business Account.

  • Connect it to a Facebook Page.

WhatsApp:

  • Get a verified WhatsApp Business Number.

  • Sign up for WhatsApp Business API via Meta or a provider like Twilio, 360dialog, or Zoko.

—

✅ 2. Choose a Chatbot Platform (No-code or Low-code)

Use a platform that supports both Instagram & WhatsApp:

  • Twilio Studio

  • Wati

  • Zoko

  • Landbot

  • Yellow.ai

  • Meta’s own Messenger Platform (requires more development)

—

✅ 3. Design Chatbot Flow

Here’s a sample flow for your perfume bot:

👋 Hi! Welcome to ITRA Bazaar.
Let me help you discover your perfect scent. 🌸

1️⃣ What occasion is the perfume for?
[ Romantic 💖 | Daily ☀️ | Festive 🎉 | Work 💼 ]

2️⃣ What scent type do you prefer?
[ Woody 🌲 | Floral 🌹 | Fruity 🍊 | Spicy 🌶️ ]

3️⃣ Here's your match!
We recommend: “Black Oud” — a bold, royal itra with long-lasting notes of agarwood & rose.
[🛒 View Product] [💬 Start Over]

🛍 Optionally collect:

  • User name

  • Email (for offers)

  • Feedback or review

—

✅ 4. Train AI / Integrate with GPT (optional)

If you want an AI-like experience (ChatGPT-style) instead of just buttons:

  • Use OpenAI's GPT API to generate answers

  • Middleware can process user messages, convert them to API prompts, and return answers

  • Hosting via Node.js, Python (Flask), or Firebase Functions

—

✅ 5. Connect to Instagram + WhatsApp

For Instagram:

  • Use Instagram Messaging API via Meta for Developers

  • Register a webhook for messages

  • Use platforms like ManyChat or Zoko for easier setup

For WhatsApp:

  • Connect via Twilio or 360dialog

  • Host your logic on backend (or integrate via chatbot builder)

  • Apply for message templates (for proactive outreach)

—

✅ 6. Test and Launch

  • Test both flows in sandbox first

  • Enable auto-reply outside business hours

  • Monitor analytics: click-throughs, popular queries, drop-off points
